### Phase 1: State Management

**Q1.1: State backend configuration**

| Aspect | Value | Risk |
|--------|-------|------|
| Backend type | S3 / GCS / Terraform Cloud / Local | |
| State locking enabled | Yes / No | |
| Encryption at rest | Yes / No | |
| State versioning / history | Yes / No | |
| Remote state access controls | | |

- [ ] State is never committed to version control
- [ ] State locking prevents concurrent apply conflicts
- [ ] State can be recovered from version history if corrupted
- [ ] Sensitive outputs are marked sensitive or excluded

**Q1.2: State isolation**

| Environment | State Path / Workspace | Shared Resources? |
|-------------|------------------------|-------------------|
| Development | | |
| Staging | | |
| Production | | |

- [ ] Each environment has isolated state (no shared state files)
- [ ] Production state has restricted access
- [ ] Workspace or directory separation is documented

